Why Lazarus Management Co Llc Just Disclosed Huge New Authentidate Holding Corp Stake


04/29/2015  by OctaStaff 
			in SEC 13G & 13D Filings 












Share with your friendsYour NameYour EmailRecipient EmailEnter a MessageI read this article and found it very interesting, thought it might be interesting for you. The article is called Why Lazarus Management Co Llc Just Disclosed Huge New Authentidate Holding Corp Stake and is was published by Octafinance.com at http://www.octafinance.com/why-lazarus-management-co-llc-just-disclosed-huge-new-authentidate-holding-corp-stake/33897/.CaptchaSubmitLazarus Management Co Llc New Position in Authentidate Holding Corp. (NASDAQ:ADAT)
Lazarus Management Co Llc has filled a SC 13D/A form regarding Authentidate Holding Corp  1.52 0.00 0.00%. Per Lazarus Management Co Llc’s filing, the filler now owns 29.4% of the Information Technology-company, holding 14,718,034 shares.
 Authentidate Holding Corp. (NASDAQ:ADAT) is a newly disclosed equity position  and the filing was required due to activity on April 24, 2015. This most probably shows Lazarus Management Co Llc’s confidence and optimism in the future of the company.
Why Lazarus Management Co Llc Bought Authentidate Holding Corp
Item 4.Purpose of Transaction

Item 4 of the Schedule 13D is hereby supplemented by adding the following:

On April 24, 2015, Lazarus Partners purchased a promissory note from the Issuer in the principal amount of $500,000, bearing interest at 0.48% per month, with principal and interest payable on the maturity date. The note is scheduled to mature on July 2, 2015 or at such earlier time as the Issuer receives at least $900,000 in cash proceeds during a 30-day period from an equity or debt financing. In connection with the purchase of the promissory note, the Issuer and Lazarus Partners entered into a Warrant Amendment Agreement, dated April 24, 2015, pursuant to which the terms of warrants to purchase common stock held by Lazarus Partners were amended by extending the expiration date to October 25, 2019 and adjusting the exercise price to $0.25 per share. Lazarus Partners beneficially owns warrants to purchase 6,233,634 shares of common stock to which these amended terms apply. With respect to warrants to purchase 4,001,240 shares of common stock, the effective date of the amendment was April 24, 2015 and with respect to warrants to purchase 2,232,394 shares of common stock, the effective date is May 7, 2015.

Authentidate Holding Corp Hedge Funds Ownership
Latest SEC filings show 20 hedge funds and institutional investors own Authentidate Holding Corp. The institutional ownership of the company in Q4 2014 is low, at 6.19% of the shares outstanding. They decreased by 521124 the total shares they hold. As of that quarter these institutional investors owned 2585541 shares. A total of 4 funds opened new positions in Authentidate Holding Corp and 3 increased their holdings. There were 2 funds that closed their positions and 3 that reduced them.
 J-P Turner & Company Capital Mnagement Llc is the most positive institutional investor on Authentidate Holding Corp, with ownership of 115947 shares as of Q4 2014 for 0.11% of the fund’s portfolio.  Great Lakes Advisors Llc is another positive player owning 40000 shares of the company or less than 0.01% of their stocks portfolio. OH Keybank National Association have less than 0.01% of their stock portfolio invested in the stock for 11650. Further, Commonwealth Equity Services Inc disclosed it had purchased a stake worth less than 0.01% of the fund’s stock portfolio in the company. The PA Pnc Financial Services Group Inc was also a notable investor in the firm, owning 35700 shares. Authentidate Holding Corp is less than 0.01% of the fund’s stock portfolio.
Company Profile
Authentidate Holding Corp. (Authentidate) is engaged in providing web-based software applications and telehealth products and services. The Company’s web-based services are delivered as Software as a Service (SaaS) to its customers interfacing with billing, information and document management systems. Its products include Inscrybe Healthcare, Electronic House Call and Interactive Voice Response Telehealth Solutions, Inscrybe Office and AuthentiProof. These solutions incorporate features and security technologies such as business-rules based electronic forms, intelligent routing, transaction management, electronic signatures, identity credentialing, content authentication, automated audit trails and remote patient monitoring capabilities. The Company sells its web-based services and telehealth products, and services through a direct sales effort, reseller arrangements and group purchasing organizations (GPO).

Form 13D is SEC filing that must be submitted within 10 days, by anyone who acquires beneficial ownership of more than 5% of any publicly traded securities. A filer must promptly update its 13D filing in case of acquisition or disposition of 1% or more of the securities that are the subject of the filing. These filings may be a precursor to hostile takeovers, company breakups, and other “change of control” events.

